---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import Lead from "../../components/Lead.astro";
import NextSteps from "../../components/NextSteps.astro";
import { url } from "../../lib/url";
---

<Base
  title="How this site is funded"
  description="It isn't. No ads, no affiliates, no sponsors, no paid placements — and what that means for you."
  crumbs={[]}
>
  <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl">How this site is funded</h1>
  <Lead>
    It isn't. Nothing here earns money — no ads, no affiliate links, no
    sponsors, no paid placements, no products, no email list to sell you
    anything later.
  </Lead>

  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      That's a deliberate choice, and it's load-bearing. Because no income
      rides on any approach looking good, this site can grade things honestly —
      recommend the free thing, tell you when the evidence is thin, note when a
      popular method is contested, and point you somewhere else entirely if
      that's what would actually help.
    </p>
    <p>
      If that ever changes — if there's ever a cost to keep it running, or any
      money involved at all — this page will say so first, plainly, before you
      run into it anywhere else.
    </p>
    <p>
      There's no catch to look for. It's just here.
    </p>
  </div>

  <NextSteps>
    <li><a href={url("about/criteria/")}>How the directory is curated</a></li>
    <li><a href={url("about/why/")}>Why this site exists</a></li>
    <li><a href={url("modalities/")}>The modality directory</a></li>
  </NextSteps>
</Base>
